(Definition) Tj
ET
1 1 1 RG
2 w
60 430 m 660 430 l S
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 370 Td
(Let A be an n x n matrix. A scalar L is an eigenvalue of A) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 338 Td
(if there is a nonzero vector v with) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 274 Td
(        A v = L v) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 210 Td
(Such a v is called an eigenvector of A for L.) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 178 Td
(The set of all such v, together with 0, is the eigenspace.) Tj
ET
endstream
