(Diagonalisation) Tj
ET
1 1 1 RG
2 w
60 430 m 660 430 l S
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 370 Td
(If A has n linearly independent eigenvectors, collect them) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 338 Td
(as the columns of P. Then) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 274 Td
(        P^-1 A P = D) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 210 Td
(where D is diagonal and holds the eigenvalues.) Tj
ET
BT
/F2 18 Tf
1 1 1 rg
60 178 Td
(Powers become cheap: A^k = P D^k P^-1.) Tj
ET
endstream
